{
	"name": "Silent Cacophony",
	"type": "spell",
	"img": "icons/creatures/magical/spirit-earth-stone-magma-yellow.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Conducting a silent orchestra with a baton, you overwhelm your target with deafening noise coming from nowhere. The sound can take any form: a roaring orchestra, deafening chattering, or even just white noise.</em></p><p><strong>Wisdom</strong> <strong>Save</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 4d6 psychic]] damage* and is &amp;reference[deafened]. Target rolls again at end of their turns, taking damage again and ending effect on success.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half initial damage, no other effect.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 1d6 psychic]]{1d6} for each spell level above 3rd.</p><p><em>Unlike most illusions, &amp;reference[truesight] does not help defend against Silent Cacophony.</em></p>",
			"chat": "<p><strong>Wisdom</strong> <strong>Save</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 4d6 psychic]] damage* and is &amp;reference[deafened]. Target rolls again at end of their turns, taking damage again and ending effect on success.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half initial damage, no other effect.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 1d6 psychic]]{1d6} for each spell level above 3rd.</p>"
		},
